headline: 1 Consumer Stock with Promising Prospects and 2 to Brush Off
summary: Consumer staples stocks are solid insurance policies in frothy markets ripe for corrections. Surprisingly, the sector hasn’t played its shielding role over the past six months as it tumbled 13.9%. This drop was noticeably worse than the S&P 500’s 1.9% decline.
